      "id": "d3",
      "title": "Binary vs Counting Semaphore",
      "type": "comparison",
      "content": {
        "binary": {
          "range": "0 or 1",
          "use": "Mutual exclusion",
          "example": "Lock/unlock",
          "ownership": "No ownership tracking"
        },
        "counting": {
          "range": "0 to N",
          "use": "Resource pool access",
          "example": "N database connections",
          "ownership": "No ownership tracking"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "d4",
      "title": "Semaphore Usage Patterns",
      "type": "list",
      "content": {
        "items": [
          "Mutual Exclusion: mutex=1; wait(mutex); critical section; signal(mutex)",
          "Ordering: sync=0; Process A does S1 then signal(sync); Process B does wait(sync) then S2",
          "Resource Counting: resources=N; wait(resources) to acquire; signal(resources) to release"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "d5",
      "title": "Common Pitfalls",
      "type": "list",
      "content": {
        "items": [
          "Deadlock: wait(A);wait(B) in P1 vs wait(B);wait(A) in P2 creates circular dependency",
          "Missing signal: process never releases, others starve",
          "Missing wait: no synchronization occurs",
          "Wrong order: signal before wait breaks ordering guarantee"
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
